cs.PL, cs.AR, cs.OS, cs.DC, cs.SE 

The paper discusses the implementation of the Java Memory Model in a Java Virtual Machine targeting a non-cache-coherent memory architecture. This involves discussions on programming languages, memory models, and virtual machines, which are all related to the sub-categories of programming languages (cs.PL), architecture (cs.AR), operating systems (cs.OS), distributed computing (cs.DC), and software engineering (cs.SE). However, since the paper focuses on the implementation of the Java Memory Model, programming languages (cs.PL) and architecture (cs.AR) are the most likely sub-categories.
